{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"padding","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"edges","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Edge","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Set","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO3SetV","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" = .all, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"length","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGFloat","preciseIdentifier":"s:14CoreFoundation7CGFloatV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"edges","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The set of edges to pad for this view. The default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set\/all"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"name":"length","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An amount, given in points, to pad this view on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified edges. If you set the value to ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", OpenSwiftUI uses","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a platform-specific default amount. The default value of this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parameter is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that’s padded by the specified amount on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified edges."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this modifier to add a specified amount of padding to one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"edges of the view. Indicate the edges to pad by naming either a single"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value from "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set"},{"type":"text","text":", or by specifying an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/Swift\/OptionSet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contains edge values:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text padded by 20 points on the bottom and trailing edges.\")","        .padding([.bottom, .trailing], 20)","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The order in which you apply modifiers matters. The example above","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applies the padding before applying the border to ensure that the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"border encompasses the padded region:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can omit either or both of the parameters. If you omit the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"length"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI uses a default amount of padding. If you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"omit the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"edges"},{"type":"text","text":", OpenSwiftUI applies the padding to all edges. Omit both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to add a default padding all the way around a view. OpenSwiftUI chooses a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default amount of padding that’s appropriate for the platform and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the presentation context."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text with default padding.\")","        .padding()","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above looks like this in iOS under typical conditions:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To control the amount of padding independently for each edge, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"View\/padding(_:)-6pgqq","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". To pad all outside edges of a view by a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified amount, use ","type":"text"},{"code":"View\/padding(_:)-68shk","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"10.15","name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"tvOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0",